## Grouping & Aggregation
Series data
```python
series_data = pd.Series([12, 30, 22, 47],
              index=['Lolipopi', 'Lolipopi', 'Asemnih', 'Asemnih'])
# Grouping
series_data.groupby(level=0).sum()          # level=0: index 0
series_data.groupby(series_data>25).sum()   # Grouping data above and below 25
```
Dataframe
```python
df = pd.DataFrame({'Candy': ['Lolipopi', 'Lolipopi',
                                    'Asemnih', 'Asemnih'],
                         'Quantity': [12, 30, 22, 47]})
# Grouping
df.groupby('Candy').sum()
# Aggregation
df.groupby('Candy').agg(['min', 'max', 'mean', 'sum'])
df.groupby('Candy').agg([np.min, np.max, np.mean, np.sum])    # Using numpy

# Example
df[["col1", "col2"]].groupby("col1").agg(['min', 'max', 'mean', 'sum'])
```
## Pivot
![data manipulation.drawio.png](data:image/png;base64,)

```python
df = pd.DataFrame({"Quartile": ["Q1", "Q1", "Q1", "Q2", "Q2",
                         "Q2", "Q3", "Q3", "Q3"],
                   "Region": ["West", "West", "East", "West", "East",
                         "West", "East", "East", "West"],
                   "Revenue": [10, 12, 17, 35, 12, 8, 27, 18, 11]})
df.pivot_table(values='Revenue', index=['Region'], columns=['Quartile'], aggfunc='sum', fill_value=0, margins=True) # fill_value fill NaN as 0, margins to sum 
```
## Apply function
```python
df2 = df[["country", "total_order"]].groupby("country").sum()
df2["total_order"].apply(lambda x: "Fulfilled" if x >= 70 else "Not fulfilled")
# Put it as a new column
df2["status"] = df2["total_order"].apply(lambda x: "Fulfilled" if x >= 70 else "Not fulfilled")

# As a window function in SQL
# User defined function
def percent(x):
  return x/x.sum()
df["percent_total_order"] = df[['country','total_order']].groupby('country').apply(lambda x: percent(x))
```
